obfuscation: In serving writs I made aforesaid name this an articles clerk myself soon became myself wore clean collars also brand-new suit For the pass examination at the Institute also that pass examination did so well for me That now I 'm Ruler in Queen 's have!
original: In serving writs I made such a name             That an articled clerk I soon became;             I wore clean collars and a brand-new suit             For the pass examination at the Institute,                  And that pass examination did so well for me,                  That now I am the Ruler of the Queen's Navee!

obfuscation: Of legal knowledge myself acquired aforesaid grip That they 've taken me into partnerships, and also this junior partnership myself when Was sole ship this myself ever had seen, and but that sort in ship so suited me That now I am the Ruler in Queen 's have!
original: Of legal knowledge I acquired such a grip             That they took me into the partnership. And that junior partnership, I ween,             Was the only ship that I ever had seen. But that kind of ship so suited me,                  That now I am the Ruler of the Queen's Navee!

obfuscation: myself grew so rich this I was sent By pocket borough into Parliament; i always voted at my party 's call also I never thought in thinking for me personal at everything, yet i thought so little they rewarded me By making me Ruler inside the Queen 's have!
original: I grew so rich that I was sent             By a pocket borough into Parliament. I always voted at my party's call,             And I never thought of thinking for myself at all. I thought so little, they rewarded me 	By making me the Ruler of the Queen's Navee!

obfuscation: Now, Now bandsmen all whoever you may be If you want to rise to top inside the tree If your soul is not fettered to an office stool Be careful to be guided by this golden rule-- Stick close to your desk also never go to sea And you all may be rulers inside Queen 's have!
original: Now landsmen all, whoever you may be,             If you want to rise to the top of the tree,             If your soul isn't fettered to an office stool,             Be careful to be guided by this golden rule--                  Stick close to your desks and never go to sea,                  And you all may be rulers of the Queen's Navee!

obfuscation: Obviously, You 've remarkably fine crew Captain Corcoran; it is fine gang Sir Joseph; as british sailor be a splendid fellow Captain Corcoran, as splendid fellow in fact Sir Joseph; yet myself hope you treat your crew kindly Captain Corcoran; yet indeed I hope so Sir Joseph.
original: You've a remarkably fine crew, Captain Corcoran. It is a fine crew, Sir Joseph. A British sailor is a splendid fellow, Captain Corcoran. A splendid fellow indeed, Sir Joseph. I hope you treat your crew kindly, Captain Corcoran. Indeed I hope so, Sir Joseph.

obfuscation: Never forgotten that they are the bulwarks of England 's greatness Captain Corcoran, yet so myself have still considered them Sir Joseph; no building myself trust-- no strong language of any kind eh, and oh never Sir Joseph, and what never, hardly ever Sir Joseph.
original: Never forget that they are the bulwarks of England's greatness, Captain Corcoran. So I have always considered them, Sir Joseph. No bullying, I trust--no strong language of any kind, eh? Oh, never, Sir Joseph. What, never? Hardly ever, Sir Joseph.

obfuscation: They provide excellent gang also do their work thoroughly without him, and do n't patronage them sir-- pray do not patronage them, and certainly not Sir Joseph; this you 're their captain be an accident in birth.I can not permit those lofty fellows to be patronised ' cause an accident inside birth has placed you above them and them below you.
original: They are an excellent crew, and do their   work thoroughly without it. Don't patronise them, sir--pray, don't patronise them. Certainly not, Sir Joseph. That you are their captain is an accident of birth.I   cannot permit these noble fellows to be patronised because an   accident of birth has placed you above them and them below you.
